{
  "texts": [
    "Regrettably, large medical imaging datasets containing task-or pathology-specific labels for all constituent examples do not exist in abundance [7].",
    "Moreover, medical imaging datasets tend to contain far fewer examples than the photographic image datasets driving much of the recent progress in computer vision [8].",
    "Obstacles such as patient privacy concerns, private corporate interests, and the need for expert labelling, hamper the production and dissemination of such datasets [9,10].",
    "Occasionally, situations arise in which unlabelled datasets of medical images are available.",
    "Labelling a complete dataset requires established expertise, the cost of which dwarfs the cost of crowdsourcing labels."
  ]
}